[Patient] "Can you give me some recommendations for managing my fluid intake?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Sure! Try to limit your salt intake and keep track of how much fluid you drink."
[Patient] "How much water should I be drinking each day?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Around 8 cups of water a day is a good goal for most people."
[Patient] "What should I do if I start to feel bloated or short of breath?"
[Healthcare Educator] "If you notice those symptoms, let your doctor know right away. It could be a sign of fluid overload."
[Patient] "Should I be worried about drinking too much water?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Yes, too much water can put a strain on your heart. Stick to the recommended amount."